15. CRASH RECOVERY WITH UUID KEYING
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
External editor sessions spawn background autosave thread.
Every 30 seconds, temporary file content is saved to:

    .recovery/{note_title}_{uuid[-6:]}.{ext}

Recovery file contains:
    - note_uuid, parent_notebook_uuid
    - content, is_file_note flag, file_extension
    - note_title, last_updated timestamp

On notebook access, recovery system checks for orphaned files:
    - Scan recovery directory for files matching notebook UUID
    - For each file, check if note exists in current structure

Two recovery scenarios:

CREATION RECOVERY (note never saved)
    - Note UUID not found in current structure
    - Create new Note object with recovered content
    - Add to notebook, save silently
    - Commit creation to Git with proper metadata
    - Clean up recovery file

MODIFICATION RECOVERY (note crashed during edit)
    - Note UUID found in current structure
    - Compare recovery timestamp with note.updated
    - If recovery newer, replace content
    - Save silently, commit edit to Git
    - Clean up recovery file

Recovery is silent and automatic:
    - No user interruption unless content restored
    - One notification of recovered count
    - All operations logged for debugging

Recovery files cleaned after 24 hours if orphaned.

